25:35.577 --> 25:37.448
You can do anything
you put your mind to!

25:38.188 --> 25:39.842
If you see it,
you can achieve it.

25:39.886 --> 25:41.235
- Let's go!
- Excuse me.

25:42.105 --> 25:43.846
- Lola Carmichael?
- Yeah.

25:43.890 --> 25:47.023
I'm officer Bernard.
My partner, officer Cohen.

25:47.067 --> 25:48.634
We'd like to talk
about the gift card

25:48.677 --> 25:49.852
you used for this class.

25:49.896 --> 25:51.419
Would you come
with us, please?

25:51.941 --> 25:53.116
Yeah.

26:02.343 --> 26:05.607
Tomorrow the prosecution
will call more witnesses,

26:05.651 --> 26:08.088
including the criminalists
that worked with investigators

26:08.131 --> 26:09.698
on your case--
Let me guess,

26:09.742 --> 26:12.092
you grew up
in an upper-middle class home,

26:12.135 --> 26:13.528
went to one of them

26:13.572 --> 26:16.487
highfalutin
private schools, hmm?

26:16.531 --> 26:20.274
Probably only dated
rich white women, huh?

26:20.317 --> 26:23.669
Your mommy and daddy
spoil you rotten, I can tell.

26:24.800 --> 26:26.106
Look.

26:26.933 --> 26:28.761
Carl, I get it.

26:29.544 --> 26:31.502
I get that
you had it rough growing up.

26:31.546 --> 26:33.287
Your sister,
she told me about your--

26:34.244 --> 26:35.594
the troubles you faced.

26:36.290 --> 26:37.552
It's a lot.

26:37.596 --> 26:39.336
Your father's
untimely death...

26:40.207 --> 26:42.775
your mom leaving you
with your grandparents--

26:44.211 --> 26:47.475
Don't talk about
my mother, you understand?

26:48.998 --> 26:51.087
Don't ever talk about her.

26:53.046 --> 26:54.525
It's okay, deputy.

26:54.569 --> 26:56.353
Just give us
a minute, please.

27:04.492 --> 27:06.625
I don't know
if my sister told you...

27:07.887 --> 27:10.541
but after our mother left,

27:10.585 --> 27:13.588
she came back,
years later,

27:13.632 --> 27:15.634
when she
found out about my cancer.

27:16.809 --> 27:18.245
She was a match

27:18.288 --> 27:20.769
and she wanted
to donate her bone marrow.

27:20.813 --> 27:24.643
Yeah,
and I was so happy.

27:25.165 --> 27:27.471
My momma
came back to save me.

27:29.430 --> 27:31.301
Then she took off again.

27:32.433 --> 27:34.522
Right before my surgery.

27:35.349 --> 27:36.785
I never knew why.

27:37.438 --> 27:41.224
All I knew was my momma
had left me a second time.

27:44.358 --> 27:45.751
She left me.

27:48.014 --> 27:51.974
That bitch
left me to die.

28:16.869 --> 28:18.087
Thanks.

28:18.131 --> 28:19.741
And thanks
for showing up.

28:19.785 --> 28:22.657
You think I wouldn't?
I wasn't-- I'm not--

28:26.139 --> 28:27.575
Can I
ask you a question?

28:28.228 --> 28:29.359
You ever worry
about charging

28:29.403 --> 28:30.839
the wrong guy with murder?

28:30.883 --> 28:32.275
Just curious.

28:32.319 --> 28:34.016
I tend to worry
about the guilty guy

28:34.060 --> 28:35.322
getting away with it.

28:36.149 --> 28:38.499
Look, I've been doing this
long enough to know

28:38.542 --> 28:41.894
that restorative justice
doesn't work for everybody.

28:41.937 --> 28:43.722
What the hell
is that supposed to mean?

28:44.287 --> 28:45.724
I can't
tell you everything,

28:45.767 --> 28:47.856
but we are learning
new information--

28:47.900 --> 28:49.728
New information like...
I can't tell you.

28:49.771 --> 28:51.555
Are you planning
to drop a bombshell in trial?

28:51.599 --> 28:53.732
This has nothing
to do with trial, Luke.

28:54.602 --> 28:56.517
And maybe
I shouldn't have said anything,

28:56.560 --> 28:58.432
- but I am your--
- But you sure as hell did.

28:58.475 --> 29:01.565
I'm giving you a heads up
that there is something

29:01.609 --> 29:03.785
coming down the pike, okay?

29:03.829 --> 29:06.092
And there might be
more to Carl Brewer

29:06.135 --> 29:07.397
than you think.

29:07.441 --> 29:09.095
You know
what I think, Callan?

29:09.748 --> 29:11.837
I think this is you
trying to get into my head

29:11.880 --> 29:13.099
and knock me off my game

29:13.142 --> 29:14.796
because your case
is getting weaker

29:14.840 --> 29:16.929
by the minute
and you cannot handle

29:16.972 --> 29:19.453
the thought of losing
to a public defender

29:19.496 --> 29:20.802
in his first murder trial.

29:20.846 --> 29:22.238
Are you
serious right now?

29:22.282 --> 29:23.457
Your ass
can't handle it, Callan.

29:23.500 --> 29:24.632
Wow, man. Okay.

29:24.675 --> 29:26.068
I'll see you in court.

29:44.130 --> 29:45.784
- Bailey's down.
- Mhm.

29:48.351 --> 29:49.613
Thank you, husband.

29:49.657 --> 29:50.963
You're welcome, wife.

29:52.616 --> 29:53.966
Rough day, huh babe?

29:55.924 --> 29:57.926
Well, at least they
didn't throw you in the clink.

29:57.970 --> 29:59.841
You should've let me
come down to help you.

29:59.885 --> 30:01.321
No, it was fine

30:01.364 --> 30:03.453
once I explained
everything to the officers.

30:03.497 --> 30:05.629
The point is
I got embarrassed

30:05.673 --> 30:07.414
in front of my
entire spin class

30:07.457 --> 30:09.546
because of your
little girlfriend, Nancy.

30:10.156 --> 30:13.028
I can't believe that gift card
she gave you was counterfeit.

30:13.072 --> 30:14.769
Nancy.

30:15.248 --> 30:16.727
A wanted scammer.

30:16.771 --> 30:18.947
I didn't see that one coming. Yeah.

30:18.991 --> 30:22.733
I'm as surprised
as you are, Mr. F.B.I. agent.

30:23.734 --> 30:26.912
Guess this puts a huge dent
in me and Nancy's relationship.

30:28.000 --> 30:30.350
It's too soon, Robin.

30:30.393 --> 30:32.874
Too soon.

30:34.876 --> 30:36.138
I'm sorry, baby.

30:36.791 --> 30:38.619
I guess I've got
some making up to do.

30:38.662 --> 30:43.102
Mhm,
but this prime rib feast

30:43.145 --> 30:44.973
is a good start.

30:45.017 --> 30:46.322
It looks delicious.

30:46.366 --> 30:47.671
Mm.

30:52.894 --> 30:53.895
Wait.

30:56.376 --> 30:59.422
Did you buy this dinner
with one of Nancy's coupons?

30:59.901 --> 31:01.424
I plead the fifth,
Your Honor.

31:19.616 --> 31:21.662
- Appreciate you coming.
- Are you kidding?

31:21.705 --> 31:23.490
I live with my brother
in his very crowded home.

31:23.533 --> 31:24.795
Of course I was coming.

31:25.753 --> 31:27.624
Congrats
on the new place, Em,

31:27.668 --> 31:29.278
- I'm happy for you.
- Oh, thank you.

31:31.585 --> 31:33.543
I mean...

31:33.587 --> 31:34.893
...I move in a week or so,

31:34.936 --> 31:37.199
and I-- I just,
I cannot wait.

31:37.243 --> 31:39.506
I look forward to my
invitation to the housewarming.

31:39.549 --> 31:41.116
Well, I look
forward to having you.

31:42.291 --> 31:45.381
So, what's up with this
new adventure of yours

31:45.425 --> 31:47.514
- they call Holistic Law?
- Yeah.

31:48.036 --> 31:50.778
I-- I told you
about the case I'm working.

31:50.821 --> 31:53.128
Single mom trying
to get her kids back.

31:53.172 --> 31:54.738
She's young, you know?

31:54.782 --> 31:57.393
And she's had
a really tough life.

31:57.437 --> 32:00.701
She-- she shared
some stuff with me...

32:01.310 --> 32:04.792
about something she experienced
that was extremely difficult.

32:05.793 --> 32:07.186
Then you share
that with the judge,

32:07.229 --> 32:08.796
and if the judge
is empathetic...

32:08.839 --> 32:11.059
It's Judge Taylor.
Judge Needum Taylor?

32:11.103 --> 32:13.061
I appeared before him
before he was transferred

32:13.105 --> 32:14.497
over to juvenile court.

32:14.541 --> 32:15.890
I'm not going to lie,
he was tough.

32:15.934 --> 32:17.457
Great.
Maybe think about

32:17.500 --> 32:18.937
holding your
most compelling argument

32:18.980 --> 32:21.069
to the very end
right before he rules.

32:21.113 --> 32:23.376
- That worked for me.
- Duly noted.

32:24.986 --> 32:27.989
- So, Luke Watkins...
- Mm.

32:28.033 --> 32:29.904
What's up with this
new adventure of yours

32:29.948 --> 32:31.775
they call public defense?

32:31.819 --> 32:33.473
I'm not going to lie.

32:34.953 --> 32:36.432
It's been tough.

32:36.476 --> 32:39.131
The trial... Callan.

32:40.654 --> 32:42.786
My client,
he shared something

32:42.830 --> 32:45.137
very painful with me
today about his mother.

32:50.055 --> 32:52.274
I could feel...

32:52.318 --> 32:54.233
the misery...

32:54.276 --> 32:55.799
that he was living with.

32:57.105 --> 32:59.629
How haunted he was,
it was--

33:07.811 --> 33:11.293
It was almost like
I could feel that misery, too.

33:15.036 --> 33:16.995
<i>Mr. Slimms,</i> <i>
thanks for getting back.</i>

33:17.038 --> 33:19.171
<i>Did you have a chance to look</i> <i>
at the case file again?</i>

33:19.214 --> 33:22.609
Bottom line, the prosecution
is saying Carl Brewer's DNA,

33:22.652 --> 33:24.045
and only his DNA,

33:24.089 --> 33:25.829
was found
on this woman's body.

33:25.873 --> 33:28.571
A lot of it. <i>
Like, too much to ignore.</i>

33:28.963 --> 33:30.660
You're going
to argue something else.

33:30.704 --> 33:32.271
The DNA is solid.

33:32.836 --> 33:34.447
Hey, listen,
I wanted to ask you again

33:34.490 --> 33:37.885
about my client's, uh,
transplant from 35 years ago.

33:37.928 --> 33:39.626
I thought you weren't allowed
to mention that in trial.

33:39.669 --> 33:41.019
<i>I'm not allowed to talk about</i>

33:41.062 --> 33:42.846
my client's current
medical condition,

33:42.890 --> 33:44.674
but no one said I can't refer
to his medical history.

33:44.718 --> 33:46.024
<i>Well,</i> <i>
you're the lawyer.</i>

33:46.807 --> 33:47.851
Wait a minute.

33:49.331 --> 33:50.593
What kind of transplant
did you say your client had?

33:54.554 --> 33:56.947
I've heard all that
I'm going to hear, Miss Lopez.

33:56.991 --> 33:58.688
I would just like
to say one more thing

33:58.732 --> 34:00.125
on behalf of Miss Collins.

34:00.168 --> 34:02.127
She recently
shared with me something

34:02.170 --> 34:04.346
that she experienced that was
very tough for her to handle

34:04.390 --> 34:06.870
back in British Columbia,
Canada, where she's from.

34:09.134 --> 34:12.224
There was a certain
practice called a birth alert.

34:12.267 --> 34:15.401
It allowed social workers
to flag an expecting parent,

34:15.444 --> 34:17.011
without their consent,

34:17.055 --> 34:19.666
as being unfit
to care for their child.

34:19.709 --> 34:21.407
Tell me how this
relates to the case

34:21.450 --> 34:22.756
- before me?
- Yes, Your Honor.

34:22.799 --> 34:24.888
These birth alerts
were often issued

34:24.932 --> 34:26.629
without regulation,

34:26.673 --> 34:29.067
disproportionately against
indigenous women,

34:29.110 --> 34:31.939
but also low-income
women like Charlotte.

34:32.461 --> 34:35.247
In fact, she received them
during both of her pregnancies.

34:35.290 --> 34:38.206
She spent years
on the run for fear

34:38.250 --> 34:40.904
that her children were
going to be taken from her.

34:41.383 --> 34:44.734
Judge Taylor,
please do not add to the trauma

34:44.778 --> 34:46.649
that Charlotte
has had to endure.

34:46.693 --> 34:49.174
She is a loving...
a loving mother.

34:49.957 --> 34:51.915
And she deserves
to have her children back.

35:18.812 --> 35:21.945
Sherri,
you are a lifesaver.

35:21.989 --> 35:23.643
Very welcome, Your Honor.

35:28.517 --> 35:29.823
It was a look.

35:30.345 --> 35:31.912
This incredulous look

35:31.955 --> 35:33.783
you gave me at
the Public Integrity hearing.

35:33.827 --> 35:35.959
The same look
you give to guilty defendants

35:36.003 --> 35:37.483
before you sentence them.

35:38.179 --> 35:40.834
And in that moment,
it hit me.

35:41.791 --> 35:44.707
The woman
that I have come to respect.

35:44.751 --> 35:46.448
Idolize, even.

35:46.492 --> 35:47.797
And care for.

35:48.189 --> 35:49.843
Would think
that I would steal

35:49.886 --> 35:52.585
half a million dollars
from her campaign.

35:52.628 --> 35:56.284
And though I did nothing
wrong I carry tremendous guilt,

35:56.328 --> 35:58.330
as though I had
somehow betrayed you.

35:58.765 --> 36:01.463
And for that I am angry.

36:01.507 --> 36:03.030
It really hurt.

36:04.727 --> 36:06.207
Sherri.

36:07.513 --> 36:10.733
The look I gave you
wasn't a look of scorn;

36:10.777 --> 36:13.171
it was one of concern.

36:13.214 --> 36:14.737
For the first time,
something nefarious

36:14.781 --> 36:16.478
had happened
in my backyard,

36:16.522 --> 36:19.916
and while
I never for one second

36:19.960 --> 36:22.049
believed that
you had stolen that money,

36:22.092 --> 36:23.659
someone in my camp did,

36:23.703 --> 36:26.401
and I was
worried sick about it.

36:26.445 --> 36:30.013
So, for what seemed
like an accusatory glance

36:30.057 --> 36:33.887
that I gave you,
I am truly sorry.

36:37.238 --> 36:39.066
But this look?

36:40.676 --> 36:42.112
This look right here

36:42.156 --> 36:43.940
that I'm giving you right now

36:43.984 --> 36:47.422
is a look of...

36:47.466 --> 36:50.773
admiration and appreciation

36:50.817 --> 36:52.384
and of respect.

36:53.298 --> 36:56.779
It is a look of love
and of apology.

37:01.306 --> 37:02.524
Thank you.

37:09.139 --> 37:12.099
Miss Collins,
you've missed court-mandated

37:12.142 --> 37:13.883
therapy sessions,
you've missed A.A. meetings,

37:13.927 --> 37:16.364
you're someone
who does not obey rules.

37:16.408 --> 37:17.670
That is a problem.

37:18.279 --> 37:20.412
Having said all that,
I strongly believe

37:20.455 --> 37:23.241
in a concerted effort
to strengthen the relationship

37:23.284 --> 37:26.287
between parents involved in
the system and their children.

37:27.332 --> 37:29.290
Miss Lopez is right,
you've been through a lot

37:29.334 --> 37:32.380
and I'm convinced you never put
your children in harm's way.

37:33.076 --> 37:35.209
I'm ruling that your
children be returned to you

37:35.253 --> 37:37.820
while you serve out the terms
of your plea agreement.

37:37.864 --> 37:39.257
Thank you.

37:39.300 --> 37:41.781
Thank you so much.

37:59.015 --> 38:00.756
We sent
the blood for processing

38:00.800 --> 38:02.323
and we found that
the genetic profile

38:02.367 --> 38:05.021
generated from the blood
found on the victim's body

38:05.065 --> 38:07.894
was consistent
with Carl Brewer's DNA profile.

38:09.983 --> 38:11.332
Thank you.

38:11.376 --> 38:12.812
Mr. Watkins.

38:14.727 --> 38:16.294
Miss Reed.

38:16.337 --> 38:18.470
Just to be clear,
you told this Jury

38:18.513 --> 38:21.473
that the DNA from the victim
and the DNA from my client

38:21.516 --> 38:24.084
matched to a certainty of,
what was it,

38:24.127 --> 38:26.478
- one in 19 billion?
- Correct. Right.

38:26.521 --> 38:28.784
19 billion,
that's a big number.

38:28.828 --> 38:30.438
Three times
the total population

38:30.482 --> 38:32.310
of humans on the planet.

38:33.006 --> 38:35.269
Even with that certainty,
wouldn't you say that

38:35.313 --> 38:38.011
there are circumstances
in which DNA can change?

38:38.054 --> 38:39.404
Change? Uh.

38:39.447 --> 38:41.797
It's possible,
but extraordinarily rare.

38:41.841 --> 38:43.277
I want to
show you something.

38:46.846 --> 38:48.413
Know what this is,
Miss Reed?

38:49.849 --> 38:50.937
It's a Chimera.

38:50.980 --> 38:52.678
A Chimera.

38:52.721 --> 38:54.549
Comes from
Greek mythology,

38:54.593 --> 38:55.985
right?
Yes.

38:56.029 --> 38:57.857
A fire-breathing monster.

38:57.900 --> 39:00.163
A hybrid creature
made up of three different

39:00.207 --> 39:03.166
animal parts:
A lion, the body of a goat,

39:03.210 --> 39:04.690
and a snake's head for a tail.

39:05.212 --> 39:07.345
- Beautiful, actually.
- Your Honor, relevance.

39:07.388 --> 39:10.478
Overruled, I want to see
where this is going.

39:10.522 --> 39:12.480
But we're not
talking about Greek mythology,

39:12.524 --> 39:13.873
are we Mrs. Reed.

39:13.916 --> 39:16.310
Tell us how
this beautiful creature

39:16.354 --> 39:18.791
connects
to the medical definition.

39:18.834 --> 39:20.227
In medicine,

39:20.270 --> 39:23.186
Chimera refers
to a hybrid human.

39:23.230 --> 39:25.363
Someone who could be
carrying two totally different

39:25.406 --> 39:27.408
sets of DNA
inside their body.

39:27.887 --> 39:30.368
So, let's say
if someone received a procedure

39:30.411 --> 39:33.414
like, say,
a bone marrow transplant,

39:33.458 --> 39:35.503
that person
could be a Chimera, yes?

39:35.547 --> 39:37.810
They could be carrying
two distinct sets of DNA,

39:37.853 --> 39:40.813
one of the recipient
and one of the donor, right?

39:43.163 --> 39:44.860
Sorry,
I didn't hear you, Miss Reed.

39:44.904 --> 39:47.036
- Human Chimerism is rare.
- Rare, yes,

39:47.080 --> 39:49.038
but it is possible
under these circumstances.

39:49.082 --> 39:51.214
Objection, relevance.
352 in foundation.

39:51.258 --> 39:53.434
Overruled.
Continue, Mr. Watkins.

39:53.478 --> 39:56.742
Miss Reed,
if you learned that Mr. Brewer

39:56.785 --> 40:00.485
had a bone marrow transplant,
would that change your opinion

40:00.528 --> 40:03.575
regarding the probability
of the DNA evidence.

40:04.402 --> 40:05.881
Your Honor,

40:05.925 --> 40:07.927
marking defense exhibit W.

40:08.754 --> 40:12.540
Carl Brewer's medical records
from 1987 showing he received

40:12.584 --> 40:14.237
a bone marrow transplant

40:14.281 --> 40:16.022
from the California
Cancer Organization.

40:16.065 --> 40:18.633
Your Honor,
objection on prior grounds.

40:18.677 --> 40:21.288
The defense just violated
the court's rulings to prohibit

40:21.331 --> 40:23.333
the mention of the defendant's
medical record.

40:23.377 --> 40:25.466
The court didn't tell me
not to present evidence from

40:25.510 --> 40:28.295
a medical procedure that my
client received 35 years ago.

40:28.338 --> 40:30.471
You serious, Watkins?
- Bailiff, remove the jury.

40:30.515 --> 40:32.778
I ask that the evidence be
excluded and that the jurors--

40:32.821 --> 40:34.519
be instructed to disregard it.
Those records include

40:34.562 --> 40:36.259
recurrent medical records
as well as the fact that

40:36.303 --> 40:37.957
Mr. Brewer received a bone
marrow transplant.

40:38.000 --> 40:39.480
Watkins,
are you serious right now?

40:39.524 --> 40:41.264
I complied with the court's
discovery rules

40:41.308 --> 40:43.136
as well as
the court's 402 rulings.

40:43.179 --> 40:46.313
Council,
you are both out of order.

40:46.356 --> 40:47.923
I want to see you
in my chambers.

40:47.967 --> 40:49.098
Now.
